
Overview of noun pill

The noun pill has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (6) pill -- (something that resembles a tablet of medicine in shape or size)
2. (1) pill, lozenge, tablet, tab -- (a dose of medicine in the form of a small pellet)
3. pill -- (a unpleasant or tiresome person)
4. pill -- (something unpleasant or offensive that must be tolerated or endured; "his competitor's success was a bitter pill to take")
5. pill, birth control pill, contraceptive pill, oral contraceptive pill, oral contraceptive, anovulatory drug, anovulant -- (a contraceptive in the form of a pill containing estrogen and progestin to inhibit ovulation and so prevent conception)
